      "writtenOn": "2017-11-15T01:03:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "it might be better to slice this layered cake differently:\n\nfunc (d *DatacentersServer) GetDatacenters(c context.Context, req *crimson.DatacentersRequest) (*crimson.DatacentersResponse, error) {\n  // \u003cACL check\u003e\n  // Convert RPC request to a set of IDs.\n  dcs, err :\u003d getDatacenters(c, names)\n  if err !\u003d nil {\n    logging.Errorf(...)\n    return nil, grpc.Errorf(codes.Internal, ...)\n  }\n  return \u0026crimson.DatacentersResponse{\n    Datacenters: dcs,\n  }\n}\n\nThat way there\u0027ll be less repetition for error logging and converting to grpc.Errorf, and getDatacenters would be reusable from other functions (like maybe EnsureDatacenters).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 131,
        "startChar": 5,
